result.execSummary:
The defendant Jemil Lee Nance was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jemil Lee Nance in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Defendant Jemil Lee Nance in custody.  Maureen Ami Atwell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a TOTAL LENGTH of imprisonment of 3 years, consecutive to any other sentence.
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons is 1 year with credit for 4 days time served.
The Court orders the defendant to serve a maximum term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 years.

AS TO COUNT 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to a TOTAL LENGTH of imprisonment of 3 years, consecutive to any other sentence.
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons is 1 year with credit for 0 days time served.
The Court orders the defendant to serve a maximum term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 years.

The court STAYED the sentence on both counts and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 years. 

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:
Conditions of Probation/Extended Supervision to be determined by the Dept. of Corrections, but to include:

*As a condition of probation, the Court ordered the defendant to serve 6 months in the House of Correction.  Huber privileges for work, treatment and Day Reporting Center.  The Court does not object to electronic  monitoring.  The Court stayed this time to be used at the probation agent's discretion.   
*Alcohol and drug assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Mental health assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Pay child support with wage assignment ordered by the Family Court.
*Absolute sobriety.
*Random urine screens.  No positive results.
*No illegal drugs.
*No controlled substances without valid prescription.
*No contact with drug community.
*Seek and maintain full time employment.
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy.
*Obtain high school diploma or GED.

Court ordered restitution in the amount of $7078.00 to be paid to Wisconsin Support Collection Trust Fund.

- Defendant ordered no DNA sample or DNA surcharge as it has been ordered on case 15CF1165.
- Defendant advised that he may never again possess firearms or weapons.
- Civil rights suspended until reinstated.  Order received and filed.
- Pay all costs, surcharges and restitution by the end of probation, if revoked, out of up to 25% prison funds, any balance as a condition of ES.  If not paid, a civil judgment to be entered.
- Defendant does qualify for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program after serving 1 year initial confinement in this case.

Court approved participation in the Dosage Probation Pilot Program and probation may be terminated early if the defendant successfully completes the program and all other conditions of probation.
